114. Monkey patching
Monkey patching is the practice of dynamically modifying classes or functions during runtime.

# 1. Define a class with an original method
class Monkey:
    def behavior(self):
        return "Eating a banana"
# 2. Define a new function with the desired behavior
def patched_behavior(self):
    return "Playing the drums!
# 3. Apply the monkey patch at runtime
Monkey.behavior = patched_behavior

# 4. Test the modification
m = Monkey()
print(m.behavior())


