122. API Data Fetching
API data fetching is the process of requesting and retrieving data from a remote server using APIs, typically through HTTP requests.

GET: Retrieves data from a resource.
POST: Submits new data to a server.
PUT / PATCH: Updates existing resources.
DELETE: Removes a resource from the server.

import requests
response = requests.get("https://api.example.com/users")


